description: Disc Medicine, Inc., a clinical-stage biotechnology company, engages in discovery, development, and commercialization of novel treatments for patients suffering from serious hematologic diseases. It builds a portfolio of therapeutic candidates that address a spectrum of hematologic diseases by targeting fundamental biological pathways of red blood cell biology, primarily heme biosynthesis and iron homeostasis. The company is based in Watertown, Massachusetts.
ceo: Dr. John D. Quisel Esq., J.D., Ph.D.
